reviews.text: The architecture of the building it is situated in is interesting, and there are some paintings by famous Romanian artists, but I expected to see more paintings, maybe some by internationally painters, which was not the case.
One of the remarkable buildings, represents an important era which defines the history of the city. Unfortunately it is in deplorable condition.
A place to visit for Art lovers. One of the best spot around the center. It’s a must to see!
Very nice.Fine building.Easy accessible
Romanian artists with rare paintings.it is a very good way to understand the Romanian art evolution. The guide is recommended.was well informed and pleasant.

Nothing is related to Pazhassi Raja. It’s just a honour to him.

Museum is at east hill which was one of administrative block of British rule in Malabar. Well maintained and guide at museum help us to know the history of all artefacts displayed. No photos allowed. Best for one day trip especially school children.
A nice sport for relaxation and also a heritage place. Alots of things to study and a wonderful experience will get from there. Need to go there

Some interesting artefacts here. But the low budget allocation is obvious. They have done the best they can to maintain the museum, but the lack of resources is a big let down. And the artefacts themselves are nothing to write home about. A few clay pots and weapons catch your attention. 

Visit, if only if you are in the area.

This is located near to Calicut staff over here are not cooperative. you have to keep the exact change in your hand otherwise they will not I love you inside if you don't have change there is no option to enter inside.. card swiping also not available...
Quite informative; came across articles og bygone era. Engrossing. The guide ther, English speaking, trained was quite helpful. Time usefully spent..

Loved all of the accompanying dishes so you can create your own flavor combos. We got there just in time, around 6:30 before the mobs of people started to arrive around 7. The service was terrific, fast, warm smiles and the staff all had a collective effort. Be sure to say hi to the owner/host, he was the nicest guy and you can tell he took pride in his restaurant. We’ll definitely be back, but next time we’re trying the bbq table :) 

Also - be sure to get the chicken dumplings to start

It was good but I wouldn't say that it was stellar and I would come back. The food was average and the place is definitely historic. They need to up their game given there are many other fantastic korean good food options in Austin now. The place is a little hard to find as it is tucked away near a small Chinese Zen garden. The service was okay and took a while. We requested a few things but didn't get it on time. We had to ask the waiter multiple times. The interior was a little dim and bland. The tofu soup was really great though, not so sure about the cold noodles. It is worth a one time try but I can't fully recommend it as a too option, there are a lot other better ones.
We got Korean BBQ combo and everything was amazing! Great atmosphere, very helpful staff. Loved it!!
Have been coming here for ten years plus. Never a bad experience! Great atmosphere, and wonderful people.

Always great. They have cleaned, updated and renovated the place. They also performed a menu update after the previous owner, who was also the sushi chef, retired. No more sushi is a bummer. Also, my favorite dish consisting of stir fried baby octopus is gone. I was initially sad that my favorite dish was gone but it forced me to try something new and I was not let down! They were busy for lunch and all the diners seemed content. I will always come back.

My girlfriend and I visited Fujiyama on a Saturday night. And they were packed!  it is a beautiful restaurant with a great ambience.  We were seated rather quickly. It took the waitress a little while to come and take our order. After waiting for our order for over an hour we asked the waitress if we can get it to go. It was brought out minutes later.  If the wait wasn’t so long I’d give this place five stars.

The sushi on the other hand was absolutely amazing!  We ordered five separate rolls and each one was better than the last.

This place is definitely a five-star restaurant but when they get packed on the weekends it is crazy.

We will definitely be going back to Fujiyama in the future but next time we’ll get our order to go.

Great place for a special lunch.  Food is always amazing, staff is friendly and helpful.  Some visits may have been better then others but that has nothing to do with the food.  I really love the ambiance of the place.. you get a great feeling when you walk in and it all makes for s great dining experience.  😋

I went here for my grandmother's birthday and we had the best night! The staff is so kind and I believe the manager personally sang happy birthday to her. I recommend anyone to come here if they have the time.

Fujiyama is a fun place to go with a crowd. For the past several years my niece has selected this hibachi restaurant as her go to place for a birthday party that includes family and close friends. The chef does his best to entertain guests with a little cooking show. Although I can't help but think he is laughing at us peasants as he tosses food in the air to catch in your mouth. The food is okay. Veggies, rice and shrimp are always good. Meat usually gets to dry and is not tasty. I guess that's why you get lots of sauce. The place is a bit loud so can be a challenge to hear even the person next to you. But not bad for a once a year gathering.
japanese food and the setting here is great. I like it here, great food & service. Fast, efficient, and courteous service. The bill won't break you.
